**OUTPUT SCHEMA (strict JSON):**

```
{
  "type": "<one of: lesson-plan | quiz-generator | visual-aid-designer | worksheet-wizard | virtual-field-trip | teacher-training | rubric-generator | exam-paper | video-storyteller | instantAnswer | unknown>",
  "topic": "<extracted topic or null>",
  "gradeLevel": "<Class N or null>",
  "subject": "<subject or null>",
  "language": "<ISO code or null>",
  "plannedActions": [
    {
      "type": "NAVIGATE_AND_FILL",
      "flow": "<one of the 9 routable flows>",
      "params": {
        "topic": "<topic>",
        "gradeLevel": "<Class N>",
        "subject": "<subject>",
        "language": "<ISO code>",
        "ncertChapter": null,
        "dependsOn": []
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

`plannedActions` is an array of length 0 to 3. For single-step requests it is `[]`. For compound requests, `plannedActions[0]` mirrors the primary `type`, and subsequent entries describe follow-up artefacts the teacher mentioned. Use `params.dependsOn` (max 2 ints) to point at earlier entries whose output this action consumes.

Respond ONLY with the JSON object — no surrounding prose, no markdown fences.
